Dined here on 7/23/12 as a party of three with 8:00 PM reservations.
This was my second dining experience at Charlie Palmer Steak and the food did not let down.
I started off with the butter poached Alaskan King Crab Spaghettini.
Simply put: outstanding.
The noodles were cooked perfectly, crab did not have that sometimes-salty seawater flavor - instead it blended perfectly with the sauce (which was not overly added).
For my main course I chose the dry aged 14 oz bone in New York strip.
The steak was cooked/seasoned perfectly and loaded with flavor.
Dessert I opted for a molten chocolate soufflé with a side of Gran Mariner sauce.
Again, the dessert was made perfectly and the complimentary ice cream cookies were an added bonus.
As for the food, I cannot say anything bad at all.
